<BaseLayout title="How it works · euno" description="How @euno/mcp enforces capability policy on every MCP tool call: architecture, request flow, schema parity, and the OCSF audit log." activePage="how-it-works">

    <section class="hero hero-compact">
        <div class="hero-eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span>How it works</div>
        <h1>A reference monitor <em>at the protocol boundary</em></h1>
        <p class="hero-sub">euno is a transparent MCP proxy that speaks the protocol on both ends and evaluates capability policy in the middle. The decision happens before the upstream is contacted, and every event is signed and audited.</p>
    </section>

